org.deuce.transaction.tl2cm
Class LockTable

java.lang.Object
  org.deuce.transaction.tl2cm.LockTable

public class LockTable
extends java.lang.Object

Table of locks for accessed locations. Each lock is comprised of a 64-bit number that encodes a version counter and the thread Id of the lock owner. The lock is unlocked if and only if the owner equals NO_OWNER.

The layout of the lock variable is: | owner (32 bits) | version (32 bits) |

Based on Guy Korland's and Pascal Felber's work on org.deuce.transaction.tl2.* and org.deuce.transaction.lsa*

Author:
Yoav Cohen, yoav.cohen@cs.tau.ac.il

checkAfterRead

public static int checkAfterRead(int hash,
                                 long observedLockVersion)
Checks that the location the transaction just read is still valid, i.e it's version has not changed from the one observed in checkBeforeRead and that the location is not locked.

Parameters:
hash - hash
observedLockVersion - the lock version observed by the transaction in checkBeforeRead
Returns:
-2 if the location is locked, -1 if the location's version is not as expected, 0 otherwise
